items.description:
Goodbye to the fucking internet-famous face shitÔºÅ

The biggest issue with the current large models in terms of lighting is the separation of "people" and "objects". It's as if a person was pasted into a scene, missing the depth that lighting brings, which is a significant reason why it feels so AI-esque.

So, I began trying to improve this. If one were to delve deep to address this, the top priority would be the excessive or unreasonable lighting on the characters. The best way to solve this would be to create ample backlighting, allowing the character and the environment to blend more seamlessly.

Inspired by 'Blade Runner 2049', I decided to showcase my model with a subdued color tone, a style with distinct dark and bright contrasts. I named it 'Silhouette Synthesis'.

items.name: Final Fantasy XII Architecture LoRA
items.description:
I have a form for requests; check it out if you want to request a character.

A LoRA trained on architectural images from Final Fantasy XII. Trained on NAI. Tested at 1.0-1.2 strength.

  • Trigger word is "12style".

  • Adding words like "castle", "city", or "desert" might aid in approximating the intended style.

  • Images of Archades' cityscapes were separately categorized with the tag "archades" in training, so add this tag while generating cities.

Very experimental, and I'm looking to retrain this if I can collect more varied data.

Created for the architecture collaboration. Check out my Discord if you want to take part in future collaborations (or yell at me about requests.)
